# Icons: Use lucide-react Only

This project uses **lucide-react** as its icon library.

- Always import icons from `lucide-react` — never write inline `<svg>` elements for icons.
- Custom `<svg>` is acceptable only for non-icon graphics (e.g. charts, progress rings, illustrations).

```tsx
// BAD — inline SVG icon
<svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor">
  <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7" />
</svg>

// GOOD — lucide-react
import { ArrowRight } from 'lucide-react'
<ArrowRight size={24} strokeWidth={1.2} />
```

Browse available icons at https://lucide.dev/icons before creating any custom SVG.
